trans-unit.target: Especifica um tipo de intervalo.

trans-unit.source: The DateTimeIntervalType enumeration represents date and time interval types.
trans-unit.target: A enumeração de DateTimeIntervalType representa os tipos de intervalo de data e hora.

trans-unit.source: Note that if you use the NotSet value, properties other than IntervalType or IntervalOffsetType will treat NotSet as an Auto value.
trans-unit.target: Observe que, se você usar o valor de NotSet, propriedades que não sejam IntervalType ou IntervalOffsetType tratará NotSet como um valor automaticamente.

trans-unit.source: The DateTimeIntervalType values are applicable to the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.LabelStyle>, <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.Grid>, <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.TickMark> and <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine> classes.

trans-unit.source: This value is used for grid lines, tick marks, strip lines and axis labels, and indicates that the interval type is being obtained from the <xref href="System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.Axis"></xref> object to which the element belongs.
